<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2439] File consumer - Consuming from absolute paths can cause issue on Windows when moving file when done</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2439</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using a file consumer with an absolute path, eg &lt;tt&gt;from(&quot;file:/data&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; then when the process is done and it wants to move the file to &lt;tt&gt;.camel&lt;/tt&gt; sub dir of &lt;tt&gt;/data&lt;/tt&gt; it may not do that correctly on Windows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is the logic in Camel is based upon that a path starting with \ is considered absolute, as it is on Unix OS and other platforms. Where as on Windows &lt;tt&gt;java.io.File&lt;/tt&gt; returns &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; for such files. The other return &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;. So we need to cater for this and make Windows return &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt; as well so the logic is consistent across OS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
